#ROOM
Vnum     14052
Name     &YMilitary Ward - Barracks&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     Rows of sturdy bunks fill this long chamber, each made with military
precision. Footlockers sit at the end of each bed, containing soldiers'
personal effects. Off-duty warriors rest, play cards, or maintain their
equipment. A mess hall is visible through a doorway to the &Yeast&d.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    14053
Desc      The mess hall lies to the east.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    14051
Desc      The training grounds lie to the south.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 14015 3 14052
Reset M 0 14023 2 14052
Reset O 0 14002 2 14052
Reset O 0 14003 2 14052
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     14053
Name     &YMilitary Ward - Mess Hall&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     Long wooden tables fill this dining hall, capable of seating hundreds of
soldiers at once. The smell of hearty stew and fresh bread fills the air,
and cooks work constantly in the kitchen beyond a serving window. Even
in peacetime, an army marches on its stomach.
~
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    14052
Desc      The barracks lie to the west.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 14025 2 14053
Reset M 0 14020 4 14053
Reset O 0 14010 5 14053
Reset O 0 14012 5 14053
Reset O 0 14013 3 14053
Reset O 0 14008 10 14053
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     14054
Name     &YMilitary Ward - Armory&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     Weapons and armor of every description fill this secure chamber. Racks of
rifles, axes, hammers, and swords line the walls, while suits of plate
armor stand on mannequins. Quartermasters keep meticulous records of
every piece of equipment issued to the army. The armory is the beating
heart of Ironforge's military might.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    14051
Desc      The training grounds lie to the north.
~
#ENDEXIT
