#ROOM
Vnum     14060
Name     &WThe Gryphon Roost - Entrance&d~
Sector   city~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     The tunnel opens into a massive natural cavern where the great gryphons
of Ironforge make their nests. The ceiling soars hundreds of feet overhead,
with openings to the sky that allow the beasts to come and go. The smell
of hay, feathers, and predator musk fills the air. The nesting area lies
to the &Ynorth&d, and the flight platform is to the &Ywest&d.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    14061
Desc      The nesting area lies to the north.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    14051
Desc      The Military Ward lies to the east.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    14062
Desc      The flight platform lies to the west.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 14017 1 14060
Reset M 0 14018 2 14060
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     14061
Name     &WThe Gryphon Roost - Nesting Area&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     Massive nests built from branches, hay, and shed feathers fill this section
of the cavern. Golden gryphons lounge in their nests, preening themselves
or tearing at haunches of meat. Handlers move carefully among them, earning
the trust of these magnificent but dangerous creatures.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    14060
Desc      The roost entrance lies to the south.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 14010 4 14061
Reset M 0 14017 1 14061
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     14062
Name     &WThe Gryphon Roost - Flight Platform&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     A stone platform extends out from the cavern wall, overlooking a dizzying
drop to the snowy mountains below. This is where gryphon riders mount up
and take to the skies. The wind howls through the opening, and the view
of &CDun Morogh&d is breathtaking. Saddled gryphons wait here for passengers
traveling to distant Alliance cities.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    14060
Desc      The roost entrance lies to the east.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 14009 1 14062
Reset M 0 14010 2 14062
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     14070
Name     &MTinker Town - Entrance&d~
Sector   city~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     The steady tick-tick-tick of clockwork and the occasional small explosion
announce your arrival in &MTinker Town&d, home to Ironforge's gnomish
population. Mechanical contraptions of every description whir and clank.
The gnomes took refuge here after the fall of Gnomeregan, and they have
made this district their own. The Commons lie to the &Ysouth&d, and Tinker
Town continues &Ynorth&d.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    14071
Desc      Tinker Town continues deeper.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    14002
Desc      The Commons lie to the south.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 14014 2 14070
Reset M 0 14020 2 14070
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     14071
Name     &MTinker Town - Central Workshop&d~
Sector   city~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     Chaos reigns in the best possible way here. Gnomish inventors tinker at
crowded workbenches, surrounded by gears, springs, wires, and devices of
unknown purpose. Mechanical chickens strut about, and a small steam-powered
cart trundles past carrying supplies. The air smells of oil, solder, and
burnt rubber. The engineering hall lies &Yeast&d, and the Deeprun Tram
station is to the &Ywest&d.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    14072
Desc      The engineering hall lies to the east.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    14070
Desc      The entrance lies to the south.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    14075
Desc      The Deeprun Tram station lies to the west.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 14014 3 14071
Reset O 0 14022 2 14071
Reset O 0 14023 2 14071
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     14072
Name     &MTinker Town - Engineering Hall&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     This hall serves as both workshop and classroom for Ironforge's engineers.
Blueprints cover every wall, and half-assembled devices clutter the tables.
Senior engineers lecture apprentices on the finer points of mechanical
design, while occasional sparks and bangs interrupt the lessons. A testing
chamber lies &Ynorth&d.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    14073
Desc      The testing chamber lies to the north.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    14071
Desc      The central workshop lies to the west.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 14014 2 14072
Reset O 0 14024 2 14072
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     14073
Name     &MTinker Town - Testing Chamber&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     Scorch marks and dents cover the reinforced walls of this chamber, evidence
of countless experiments gone wrong—or right, depending on your perspective.
A thick window allows observation from the relative safety of the hallway.
Currently, a gnome is attempting to activate a device that sparks ominously.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    14072
Desc      The engineering hall lies to the south.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 14014 1 14073
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     14074
Name     &MTinker Town - Gnomish Quarters&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     The gnomish refugees from Gnomeregan have made comfortable homes in these
converted chambers. The rooms are small but ingeniously designed, with
fold-out furniture and mechanical conveniences. Despite losing their
homeland, the gnomes maintain their characteristic optimism and love of
invention.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    14071
Desc      The central workshop lies to the south.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 14014 2 14074
Reset M 0 14020 3 14074
Reset O 0 14022 1 14074
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     14075
Name     &MDeeprun Tram - Ironforge Station&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     A marvel of gnomish engineering, the &WDeeprun Tram&d station gleams with
polished brass and humming machinery. This underground railway connects
Ironforge to &WStormwind City&d, crossing beneath the sea in a journey of
mere minutes. A sleek tram car waits at the platform, ready to depart.
Tinker Town lies to the &Yeast&d.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    14071
Desc      Tinker Town lies to the east.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 14014 1 14075
Reset M 0 14020 2 14075
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     14080
Name     &YThe Hall of Explorers - Entrance&d~
Sector   city~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     You enter the &YHall of Explorers&d, headquarters of the renowned
&WExplorers' League&d. Maps of distant lands cover the walls, and display
cases hold artifacts from across Azeroth and beyond. The dwarves' passion
for uncovering the secrets of the past is evident everywhere. The main
hall lies &Ynorth&d, and the Commons are to the &Ysouth&d.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    14081
Desc      The main hall lies to the north.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    14002
Desc      The Commons lie to the south.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 14012 1 14080
Reset M 0 14020 2 14080
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     14081
Name     &YThe Hall of Explorers - Main Hall&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     The main hall of the Explorers' League is a museum of wonders. Titan
artifacts gleam in enchanted cases, troll relics hang on the walls, and
a complete skeleton of an ancient beast dominates the center of the room.
Explorers share tales of distant digs, and researchers pore over ancient
texts. The library lies &Yeast&d, and a map room is to the &Ywest&d.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    14082
Desc      The library lies to the east.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    14080
Desc      The entrance lies to the south.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    14083
Desc      The map room lies to the west.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 14003 1 14081
Reset M 0 14012 2 14081
Reset O 0 14020 1 14081
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     14082
Name     &YThe Hall of Explorers - Library&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     This extensive library contains records of every expedition the Explorers'
League has ever undertaken. Journals, maps, rubbings of ancient inscriptions,
and scholarly analyses fill the shelves. Archivists catalog new discoveries
daily, adding to the ever-growing collection of dwarven knowledge.
~
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    14081
Desc      The main hall lies to the west.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 14012 1 14082
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     14083
Name     &YThe Hall of Explorers - Map Room&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     A massive table dominates this room, its surface covered with a detailed
map of the known world. Explorers gather here to plan expeditions, marking
sites of interest and routes through dangerous territory. Smaller maps
of specific regions hang on the walls, annotated with notes from previous
missions.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    14081
Desc      The main hall lies to the east.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 14003 1 14083
Reset M 0 14012 1 14083
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     14090
Name     &YThe Forlorn Cavern&d~
Sector   city~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     This quiet corner of Ironforge is home to those who prefer shadows to
firelight. Rogues and those with business best conducted in private
frequent these dimly lit passages. A still pool of water gives the
cavern its somber atmosphere. The Commons lie to the &Yeast&d, and a
tavern of questionable reputation is to the &Ynorth&d.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    14091
Desc      A shadowy tavern lies to the north.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    14002
Desc      The Commons lie to the east.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 14020 3 14090
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     14091
Name     &xThe Shady Lady Tavern&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors dark~
Desc     This dimly lit tavern caters to a clientele that prefers anonymity.
Booths with high backs line the walls, allowing private conversations.
The bartender asks no questions and remembers no faces. It's said that
information of any kind can be bought here—for the right price.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    14090
Desc      The Forlorn Cavern lies to the south.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 14004 1 14091
Reset O 0 14008 3 14091
Reset O 0 14009 3 14091
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     14095
Name     &YRam Pens&d~
Sector   city~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     The smell of hay and animal fills this large chamber where Ironforge's
war rams are stabled. The massive beasts stamp and snort in their pens,
their curling horns formidable weapons. Handlers brush their thick wool
and ensure they are well-fed and ready for service. The Commons lie to
the &Yeast&d.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    14002
Desc      The Commons lie to the east.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 14017 2 14095
Reset M 0 14018 4 14095
